text.section:
The Board may grant a waiver under this section only if the applicant:
Is of good moral character;
Pays the application fee required by the Board under § 9-303 of this subtitle;
Provides adequate evidence that:
At the time the applicant was licensed in the other state, the applicant was qualified to take the examination that then was required by the laws of this State; and
The applicant qualified for a license in the other state by passing an examination given in that or any other state.
